<div id="content">
	
	<div class="textbox">
		<h3>Description</h3>
		<div class="body">
			<p>CONTRAlign is an extensible and fully automatic parameter learning framework for protein pairwise sequence alignment based on pair conditional random fields. The CONTRAlign framework enables the development of feature-rich alignment models which generalize well to previously unseen sequences and avoid overfitting by controlling model complexity through regularization.</p>
			<p>When given as few as 20 example alignments, CONTRAlign simultaneously learns both a substitution matrix and gap penalties yielding accuracies competitive with modern alignment tools. This provides a stark contrast to traditional methods of parameter estimation, which typically require several order of magnitude more training data.</p>
		</div>
	</div>

